SandboxTesting
Project Overview
SandboxTesting is a small WinForms application created as a personal learning project focused on software development, quality assurance, testing, and documentation.
The project is inspired by my capstone proposal, which outlined a desktop catering and reservation management application built with C# and local JSON storage. For this project, the scope is intentionally much smaller. The goal is to build a lightweight reservation system that allows me to focus on learning, experimentation, and continuous improvement rather than creating a production-ready application.
Project Goals
Strengthen C# programming skills
Practice object-oriented design and application structure
Build and validate business logic
Create and execute manual test plans
Document requirements, defects, and testing results
Develop debugging and troubleshooting skills
Learn the foundations of automated testing
Build a second, more advanced version that can be used for automation practice
Technical Scope
The application will consist of:
A WinForms user interface
Basic reservation data objects
Validation and business logic
Local JSON file storage
Reservation viewing and editing capabilities
QA and Testing Focus
A major objective of this project is to approach development with a QA mindset.
This includes:
Writing requirements before implementation
Creating manual test cases
Executing and documenting tests
Identifying and recording defects
Fixing issues and validating fixes
Tracking lessons learned throughout development
Success Criteria
The project will be considered successful when:
Reservations can be created, edited, and displayed
Validation rules function correctly
Data persists using JSON storage
Manual test cases have been executed and documented
Basic automated tests have been created
Project documentation reflects both development and testing activities
Purpose
This project exists as a practical way to continue learning while job searching. It provides an opportunity to build, test, break, fix, and document a real application while developing both technical and QA-related skills in a structured and enjoyable way.


